subSubSection.paragraph:
Gall (Figs 
62-63
): Galls are located on axillary buds or young leaves on young shoots. The cross-section of the gall is triangular, with a short stalk connected to the host-plant. The gall is greenish, with a brownish tip and a greenish-brown central region, 3.9-4.6 mm long and 1.7-2.0 mm broad (n=2).
